    $( Lemma for ~ basel .  Using the binomial theorem and de Moivre's formula,
       we have the identity ` _e ^ _i N x / ( sin x ) ^ n = `
       ` sum_ m e. ( 0 ... N ) ( N _C m ) ( _i ^ m ) ( cot x ) ^ ( N - m ) ` ,
       so taking imaginary parts yields ` sin ( N x ) / ( sin x ) ^ N = `
       ` sum_ j e. ( 0 ... M ) ( N _C 2 j ) ( -u 1 ) ^ ( M - j ) `
       ` ( cot x ) ^ ( -u 2 j ) = P ( ( cot x ) ^ 2 ) ` , where
       ` N = 2 M + 1 ` . $)
    basellem3 $p |- ( ( M e. NN /\ A e. ( 0 (,) ( pi / 2 ) ) ) ->
      ( P ` ( ( tan ` A ) ^ -u 2 ) ) =
        ( ( sin ` ( N x. A ) ) / ( ( sin ` A ) ^ N ) ) ) $=
      ( wcel cc0 c2 co cexp ci cmul cc wceq syl cr syl2anc vm vk cn cdiv wa cfz
