    basel.t $e |- T = ( n e. ( 1 ... M ) |->
      ( ( tan ` ( ( n x. pi ) / N ) ) ^ -u 2 ) ) $.
    $( Lemma for ~ basel .  By ~ basellem3 , the expression
       ` P ( ( cot x ) ^ 2 ) = sin ( N x ) / ( sin x ) ^ N ` goes to zero
       whenever ` x = n pi / N ` for some ` n e. ( 1 ... M ) ` , so this
       function enumerates ` M ` distinct roots of a degree- ` M ` polynomial,
       which must therefore be all the roots by ~ fta1 . $)
