    $( Lemma for ~ basel .  Since by ~ basellem8 ` F ` is bounded by two
       expressions that tend to ` pi ^ 2 / 6 ` , ` F ` must also go to
       ` pi ^ 2 / 6 ` by the squeeze theorem ~ climsqueeze .  But the series
       ` F ` is exactly the partial sums of ` k ^ -u 2 ` , so it follows that
       this is also the value of the infinite sum
       ` sum_ k e. NN ( k ^ -u 2 ) ` . $)
    basellem9 $p |- sum_ k e. NN ( k ^ -u 2 ) = ( ( pi ^ 2 ) / 6 ) $=
      ( cn co wtru c1 cvv wcel cr cmul vx vy vz cv c2 cneg cexp csu cpi c6 cdiv
      wceq cmpt nnuz cz 1z a1i cfv oveq1 eqid ovex fvmpt adantl wa cc0 wne nnre
      wf nnne0 znegcl ax-mp reexpclz syl3anc fmptd ffvelrn sylan eqeltrrd recnd
      2z caddc cseq cli cmin cof serfre feq1i sylibr csn cxp remulcl wss fconst
