    $d k m n $.
    $( The sum of the inverse squares is ` pi ^ 2 / 6 ` .  This is commonly
       known as the Basel problem, with the first known proof attributed to
       Euler.  See ~ http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basel_problem .  This
       particular proof approach is due to Cauchy (1821).  (Contributed by
       Mario Carneiro, 30-Jul-2014.) $)
    basel $p |- sum_ k e. NN ( k ^ -u 2 ) = ( ( pi ^ 2 ) / 6 ) $=
